<subSubSection id="AA70299A3FC8C3F2EAC68555A00D0A09" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F5967D1CC4D4BE493EAB9D359DBB0EC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="889AE923D5A708604C7EF905F88C9ED4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Almost endemic to the Distrito Federal and 
<normalizedToken id="5F3DFC1817C4C8AE8BC083A76F9179DE" originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
State in Brazil. It appears to grow always in campo rupestre from around 800 m to over 1100 m. It is recorded from Mato Grosso in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction but we have seen no specimen.
</paragraph>
